<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<font color="#ff6600">Dear</font><div><font color="#ff6600"><br></font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">To ensure security against identity theft and other online fraud threats we have a number of systems in place, one of which isTwo Factor Authentication (2FA).</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600"><br></font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">In to be registered for 2FA you need to be registered on either absa online or the absa banking app.</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">To check which device you have registered as an authorisation device please follow the steps below:</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600"><br></font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">1. Logon to absa online</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">2. Select the "Full Service" tab</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">3. Select the "Profile " tab</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">4. Select "Manage Devices" row</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">5. Ensure that the device that is listed there is your primary banking device</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">6. When you transact on NovoFX, your SureCheck notification will appear on your absa banking app on that device.</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600"><br></font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">For more information, please visit your nearest absa branch</font></div><div><font color="#ff6600"><br></font></div><div><font color="#ff6600">Please note: In a case where you are registered for 2FA and your authenticating device is correct it might happen that you still won't be able to transact on the NovoFX App. We are aware of this issue and our Development Team is working on finding a resolution.</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><br></div>]]></td>
</tr>
